This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as relation extraction. Additionally, the use of neural networks and attention mechanisms further supports this categorization. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a machine learning model for relation extraction. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of ensemble learning and adaptive boosting to improve the performance of the model. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as relation extraction is a common task in information retrieval and the paper proposes a new method for improving the accuracy of this task. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for relation extraction.
